ating in the rhythms of Hasidic girlhood. Drawing on many intimate hours among Hasidim and over 30 in-depth interviews, Mystics, Mavericks, and Merrymakers offers rich portraits of individual Hasidic young women and how they deal with the conflicts between the regimented society in which they live and the pull of mainstream American life. This superbly crafted book offers intimate stories from Hasidic teenagers' lives, providing an intriguing twist to a universal theme: the struggle to grow up and define who we are within the context of culture, family, and life-driving beliefs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHabadxReligious lifezNew York (State)zNew York. 0aHabadzNew York (State)zNew YorkxSocial life and customs. 0aJewish teenagersxReligious lifezNew York (State)zNew York. 0aJewish teenagerszNew York (State)zNew YorkxSocial life and customs. 0aTeenage girlsxReligious lifezNew York (State)zNew York. 0aTeenage girlszNew York (State)zNew YorkxSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aGilligan, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilligan, Carol.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081475192340uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814753446.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814753446423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814753446/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK